HEADWORD: Shinplaster
<hw>Shin"plas`ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Formerly, a
jocose term for a bank note greatly depreciated in value; also, for
paper money of a denomination less than a dollar.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
